# GitHub push (agent)

Repo: **david9up/miditracker** · remote **origin**

## When pushing or using `gh`

1. Run git/gh commands with **full shell permissions** (not sandboxed) — sandbox blocks SSH/DNS to `github.com`.
2. **Always use HTTPS push scripts** in the agent (SSH often fails in Cursor sandbox):
   ```bash
   cd /Users/davidmalcher/Projects/miditracker
   ./scripts/push-to-github.sh          # push current branch
   ./scripts/gh-push.sh main            # low-level HTTPS push
   npm run push:github
   ```
3. Never change global git config. Never commit secrets.
4. Before push/deploy, run `./scripts/gh-auth-check.sh` — needs `repo` + `workflow` scopes.

## Pages deploy (only when user asks)

```bash
cd /Users/davidmalcher/Projects/miditracker
npm run deploy:pages
# or: ./scripts/deploy-pages.sh main
```

Do **not** deploy on every push. Deploy when the user explicitly requests it or after fixing the live site.

Live URL: **https://david9up.github.io/miditracker/**

After deploy, view-source should show `./assets/index-….js` (not `/assets/…`).

## One-time human setup

See **GITHUB_SETUP.md** — run once:

```bash
gh auth refresh -h github.com -s repo,workflow
```
